The paper proposes a technique for resource allocation in vehicular communication networks, which involves actively learning the network dynamics and estimating the vehicles' future Age of Information (AoI) to minimize the probability of AoI violation. This involves using a Gaussian process regression (GPR) approach for online decentralized learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically GPR, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves information theory, specifically in terms of resource allocation, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
